title: Highbridge
medium: graphite, pen and ink, crayon, charcoal, watercolor, and pastel on paper
credit_line: Bequest of Mr. and Mrs. James H. Beal
provenance_text:
Arthur B. Davies [1863-1928], New York, NY, until October 24, 1928; Estate of Arthur B. Davies, New York, NY, until April 17, 1929 [1]. Frank K. M. Rehn, Inc., New York, by November 1951 until 1953 [2]; purchased by Mr. and Mrs. James H. Beal, Pittsburgh, 1953 until 1993; bequest to Carnegie Museum of Art, Pittsburgh, 1993. 
NOTES: [1] Arthur B. Davies sale, American Art Association, New York, April 17, 1929, no.416? [2] see letter from Mrs. Rebecca Beal to John Clancey, Frank K. M. Rehn, Inc dated January 9, 1953
